President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Bryan David Hunt as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Sierra Leone. Hunt is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Senior Foreign Policy Advisor to the United States Transportation Command. He has held various positions within the Department of State, including Director of the Office of South Sudan and Sudan, Acting Deputy Assistant Secretary for East Africa and the Sudans, and Deputy Chief of Mission of U.S. Embassies in Mozambique, Guyana, and Papua New Guinea, among others. Hunt holds a Bachelor's degree from American University and speaks Portuguese, German, and Urdu.

Additionally, President Biden intends to nominate Felix Sanchez as a Member of the Board of Directors of the Corporation for Public Broadcasting. Sanchez is the Chairman of the National Hispanic Foundation for the Arts, which aims to advance the presence of Latinos in the entertainment industry. He has been recognized for his advocacy against Latino exclusion in entertainment and has developed pipeline programs for Latino graduate students studying theater and film at various universities. Sanchez has also served in various roles in political campaigns, including as a Legislative Assistant to former U.S. Senator Lloyd M. Bentsen Jr. and as National Deputy Campaign Manager for the Paul Simon for President campaign. He holds a B.A. and M.A. from the University of Texas at Austin and a J.D. from the University of Houston Law Center.